# InstaDM Windows — Mandatory Rules

Before any work: read `AGENTS.md`, `docs/HANDOFF.md`, `docs/IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md`,
`docs/DECISIONS.md`, `docs/PRIVACY_THREAT_MODEL.md`, and check `git status`.
Repository state wins over stale handoff prose.

## Privacy invariant (absolute)

- App-owned data never leaves the local machine except first-party
  Instagram/Meta traffic from the embedded official web client.
- Never log/store/transmit credentials, 2FA codes, cookie values, tokens,
  message content, usernames, DOM text, screenshots, or full sensitive URLs.
- Cookie checks are existence-only; never read the value.
- No analytics, telemetry, remote logging, crash upload, backend, proxy,
  cloud sync, remote config, push backend, or auto-updater — ever.
- Release builds: DevTools and remote debugging disabled.
- Never print or commit `.instadm-local.env`, WebView user data, captures,
  logs, dumps, screenshots, or signing material.
- Tests and CI use synthetic fixtures only; no live Instagram account.

## Reference material

- The macOS source repo and all Obsidian notes outside `Windows App/` are
  read-only. Only the `Windows App/` subtree may be written, with sanitized
  content only. Resolve paths from ignored `.instadm-local.env`; never commit
  or print personal absolute paths.

## Continuity

- Update `docs/HANDOFF.md` after every 3–5 meaningful actions, before long
  operations, after decisions/commits, and before ending a session. Mirror the
  identical body to `Windows App/HANDOFF.md` (repo copy first), verify equality.
- Keep the repo buildable at each commit. Run `dotnet test` for
  `InstaDM.Core.Tests` and the privacy scanners in `tools/` before committing.
- Windows-only projects build in the `windows-latest` CI workflow when the host
  is macOS; never claim a Windows build succeeded without evidence.

Rules are steering, not enforcement: the tests, scanners in `tools/`, build
configuration, and `docs/RELEASE_CHECKLIST.md` gates are the real guarantees.
Keep them intact and extend them with new code.
